<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida91962e3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s1797"><num value="1797">§ 1797.</num><heading> Early childhood education program</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Defense shall require that all military child development centers meet standards of operation necessary for accreditation by an appropriate national early childhood programs accrediting body.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida91962e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/106/dA/tV/s568/a/1">Pub. L. 104–106, div. A, title V, § 568(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1996-02-10">Feb. 10, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/335">110 Stat. 335</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
